<hr>

<p><font color="#000000">Univariate ANOVAs for all Absorption
variables were calculated across the factor of Self-Perceived
Loss of Motivation and the significant results are given in Table
8. For all three total Absorption scores (TAS, TAO and TAC)
significant differences were found with those who report more
motivation loss showing the higher levels of Absorption. Post hoc
tests reveal the differences primarily are due to the greater
Absorption means for those who lose motivation more often as
opposed to Rarely. Of the three total scores TAO shows the
highest F-ratio suggesting that those who make more opportunity
for absorptive states are most differentiated from the others.<br>
</font></p>

